Name: Space Hole 2020
About the game: Photosensitivity Warning: This game features intense procedural visual effects. Space Hole 2020 features many unpredictable visual patterns and strobing lights. Navigate mysterious cosmic structures on an allegorical journey through time Witness procedural and discovered visual effects generated by overlapping unbuffered pixels Configure dynamic visual effect bags with the Freeform Machine Journey from the origin of reality to the furthest reaches of technological expansion Non-linear design affords multiple viable paths through the game Space Hole 2020 is a standalone continuation of the Space Hole games, and like 2016 and 2018 before it, can be experienced independently (the games share only mechanical themes). Space Hole 2020 is a Sam Atlas game, Featuring music by DL Salo courtesy of Object Sonore. The game is named after the year 2020, but is neither a record of or a direct allegory for it, instead forming an existential perimeter around the year.
